# stacks/ingress/.env.example
#
# Copy to `.env` on the VPS and fill real values. `.env` is gitignored —
# never commit credentials. The values are also pasted into the NPM admin
# UI as a credentials INI block during cert creation (see ./README.md §3d);
# this file gives them one canonical home in the deploy bundle.
#
# OVH API credentials (for DNS-01 wildcard via the dns-ovh plugin):
#   1. Visit the OVH token creator for your region:
#        https://eu.api.ovh.com/createToken/    (Europe / .com domains)
#        https://api.ovh.com/createToken/       (legacy / .ca / .us)
#   2. Required grants — scope tightly to the single zone (do NOT grant
#      /domain/zone/* root):
#        GET    /domain/zone/antarctica-engineering.com/*
#        POST   /domain/zone/antarctica-engineering.com/*
#        DELETE /domain/zone/antarctica-engineering.com/*
#   3. Validity: long-lived; rotate yearly. Calendar reminder lives with
#      the admins.
#   4. Save application_key, application_secret, consumer_key on first
#      display — OVH will not show consumer_key again.
#   5. The endpoint identifier (`ovh-eu`, `ovh-ca`, `ovh-us`, etc.) must
#      match the region of the OVH account that owns the domain.

OVH_ENDPOINT=ovh-eu
OVH_APPLICATION_KEY=replace-me
OVH_APPLICATION_SECRET=replace-me
OVH_CONSUMER_KEY=replace-me
